<p>Thus far I’ve loved this entire series so I’m gonna head back and +1 everything once I’m done reading it though.</p>
<p>Only concern of mine is regarding the overpopulation of insects. If I’m remembering correctly it’s stated that this doomsday anomaly does not prevent aging or offer a healing factor. Most bugs naturally have a very short lifespan before they die. In this scenario they don’t “die” but I would assume for the most part a lot of their functions deteriorate from old age like normal? Which would prevent the whole overpopulation issue. Or I could just know nothing about bugs lol.<br />
It was just a thought of mine. It doesn’t really take away too much from the entire scenerio if it is an issue. I’m still gonna +1 everything because this whole thing is so grime and awesome to read.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">oh god the cockroaches</span></p>
<p>The whole “but the world keeps spinning” concept but now we have to suffer through it as well.</p>

