					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-lloyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1466112); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1466112&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225115" alt="Agent Lloyd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1466112)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/agent-lloyd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1466112); return false;" >Agent Lloyd</a></span> <span class="odate time_1550488125 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Feb 2019 11:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4157164">
									

<p>Okay, so, I need to clarify that the whole EoD hub is a pretty good read. But this particular article, especially its ending is just&#8230; so wrong. And I don't mean anything about how it's written. It's just this &quot;we've made animals sterile, now everything's fine, yay!&quot; that bugs me out. Seriously, <em>ecosystems do not work this way</em>.</p>
<p>Basically if you stop some species from reproducing, everything above them on the food chain will just eat out it's food supply and then starve to death, thats it. And if we are speaking insects and other vermin, whitch are going to be the main overpopulation threat in EoD scenario, than we have almost entire food chains above them. Which means that a global extinction event will hit the world in just a couple of years.</p>
<p>And even that is not all. Every flowering plant and anything else that evolved into symbiosis with some creepy-crawlies is also gone. <em>And</em> also most other plant life in a matter of decades, because, guess what, they happen to depend <em>heavily</em> on substances fron dead organics and forrowing of soil by little creatures, that the world have suddenly run out of.</p>
<p>So, in summary, such a descision would very, and I mean <em>very</em>, fast turn the world into a desolate wasteland almost devoid of life. That by itself, imho, would be an interesting topic to expand onto. But we instead get a family guy - style &quot;glad that everything is back to normal&quot; and that's it? Sorry but this is a solid downvote to me.</p>

							</div>

								
					
