			<div class="content" id="post-content-4170078">
									

<p>Obviously not everything is sterilized, just enough to keep the immediate problem of gross overpopulation at bay. In further tales there are references to medicinal maggots, and the fact that you can still eat things like steak and drink milk means that we know we can kill animals with the faith that they’ll come back.</p>
<p>Of course, you are right in pointing out that I only really talk about sterilizing insect populations, and the fact that I don’t go further into what actually gets done is an oversight on my end.</p>
<p>If I could find a way to smoothly amend this, I would. And maybe I will. I do appreciate you reading it though!</p>

